cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper deals with network security and traffic engineering, which are both subfields of computer networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses attacks and defenses, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper proposes new techniques for traffic engineering, which could be considered as a subfield of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses simulation mechanisms to evaluate the proposed defense prototypes, which could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
